# [TDD](../wg/tdd.html)

## Summary

The Technical Deep Dive (TDD) session at IETF 126 was dedicated to **CBOR** (Concise Binary Object Representation, RFC 8949) and **CDDL** (Concise Data Definition Language, RFC 8610). 

Andrew Newton introduced an expanded chair/program committee to manage future TDD sessions. Carsten Bormann then delivered a comprehensive technical presentation on the history, design choices, and security properties of CBOR, COSE (RFC 9052), and CDDL. The presentation was followed by an open discussion and Q&A focusing on developer tooling, protocol design, test vector generation, CBOR Web Tokens (CWT, RFC 8392), and future integrations with AI and Large Language Models (LLMs).

## Key Discussion Points

